snippet: Mrs. Clinton has burned through tens of millions of dollars in states unlikely to be competitive in the fall and has had to slow a pivot to the general election.
abstract: Federal Election Commission filing reveals Hillary Clinton's campaign spent more in first three months of 2016 than it took in; spending on primary campaign to contain Sen Bernie Sanders has prevented Clinton's campaign from reserving funds for general election.

byline.original: By NICHOLAS CONFESSORE and SARAH COHEN
byline.contributor: Rachel Shorey, Chase Davis and Nick Corasaniti contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Mrs. Clinton has burned through tens of millions of dollars in states unlikely to be competitive in the fall and has had to slow a pivot to the general election.

headline.main: Long Primary Carries Costs for Hillary Clinton: Money and Time
headline.print_headline: Challenge by Sanders Still Diverts Clinton From Fall
